  "permissionsIntro": "Elder Shield only uses permissions for scam protection. You can deny any permission; protection will be limited but the app still works.",
  "permissionsSmsTitle": "Messages (SMS)",
  "permissionsSmsBody": "We receive and read incoming SMS so we can analyse them for scam indicators (e.g. suspicious links, OTP phishing, bank-related wording) and show you warnings. No message content is sent off your device. You can delete all analysed history from Settings.",
  "permissionsPhoneStateTitle": "Phone (read state)",
  "permissionsPhoneStateBody": "We need to know when you're on a call so we can raise the risk level when an OTP arrives during a call (a common scam pattern). We do not record calls, listen to audio, or access your call log.",
  "permissionsPhoneCallTitle": "Phone (make calls)",
  "permissionsPhoneCallBody": "So you can tap \"Call trusted contact\" from Home or a warning. The app only starts a call when you tap the button, and only to numbers you have added as trusted contacts.",
  "permissionsNotificationsTitle": "Notifications",
